events.name: IWD Wilmington 2019

venue.name: The Mill Space, 4th Floor

events.description:
We are proud to be hosting the 2019 International Women's Day Celebration, a women's tech conference. This event will highlight the stories of our growing female community of designers, developers, and technology entrepreneurs.

As our IWD 2019 event getting closer, we want to give you a couple of updates.

Theme of the event: "Questioning the Status Quo".

Throughout history, change has often started with a question – and many of those questions have been asked by women who were bold enough to seek change.

If you are interested in sharing a story about your experience, please message Alona Matsela: https://www.meetup.com/Wilmington-Google-Developer-Group/members/223467020/profile/?returnPage=1

Snacks and refreshments will be provided.

Agenda

1:00 pm – 1:15 pm Meet and Great
1:15 pm – 1:30 pm Intro
1:30 pm – 1:50 pm Ice Breaker
1:50 pm – 2:30 pm Keynote
2:30 pm – 2:40 pm Ruffle
2:40 pm – 2:50 pm Break
2:50 pm – 3:50 pm Speakers and Q&A
3:50 pm – 4:00 pm Closing and Ruffle

Make sure to RSVP to reserve your seat, as attendance is limited.

We wanted to thank you for showing an interest in our event, and exited to meet you soon.

events.name: Super Meetup 2019

venue.name: DECO Wilmington

events.description:
Come connect with one another, make friends and learn about local tech at this year's Super Meetup!

The Super Meetup is a gathering of the most-connected members of the local tech, startup, and entrepreneurial scene. It’s a chance to make new friends and learn more about local tech and entrepreneurial resources and tech-focused meetup groups.

The idea of the Super Meetup is simple: meetups are integral to any tech scene. Every now and then, it makes sense to rally the leaders of tech-related meetups in town and gather for one big mixer. The idea is to connect people with groups they may not have otherwise known about.

Be sure to grab some food and drinks and hang with your favorite Meetups.
